body:
Hi, all.
I use a Verilator to simulate my CPU core and get bug after migration to 5 version (5.008, from Gentoo repo's). Check with current version (clone Git repo and build it) - same result.
Verilog code:
`    function static real get_ts();
        real ts = $time;
        return ts / 1000.0;
    endfunction

    function static void print_head();
        $fwrite(f, "+----------+----------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+\n");
        $fwrite(f, "| %8s | %8s | %8s | %-53s |\n", "Time", "PC", "Opcode", "Instruction/Event");
        $fwrite(f, "+----------+----------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+\n");
        $fwrite(f, "|%8.3fns|%10s|%10s| %-53s |\n", get_ts(), "", "", "Trace started.");
    endfunction

    function static void print_event(input string str);
        $fwrite(f, "|%8.3fns|%10s|%10s| %-53s |\n", get_ts(), "",  "", str);
    endfunction`

C++ file have next function:
`double sc_time_stamp() { return 0.0d; }`

And on output file, I see always "1" values: https://pastebin.com/Xc7pMhGR

Options, passed to Verilator:
VERILATOR_FLAGS += -cc --exe -j 6 --threads 10
VERILATOR_FLAGS += -x-assign fast
VERILATOR_FLAGS += -Wall
VERILATOR_FLAGS += --trace-fst --trace-structs --trace-threads 1
VERILATOR_FLAGS += --assert
VERILATOR_FLAGS += --coverage
VERILATOR_FLAGS += --build --hierarchical
VERILATOR_FLAGS += -CFLAGS "-I../../../vrf/ -I../../../sim_common/common/ -DTOP_NAME=$* -lpthread" -DTO_SIM
VERILATOR_FLAGS += -LDFLAGS "-lpthread -ljsoncpp -lfmt"
VERILATOR_INPUT = +librescan +libext+.v+.sv+.vh+.svh ../../vrf/$*.sv -f ../input.vc ../../sim_common/common/tb.cpp ../../vrf/$*.cpp
